    <h2>Strategic Property Expertise</h2>
    <p>Luxembourg's real estate market is one of the most dynamic in Europe, driven by a growing population, strong economic fundamentals and limited land supply. SAM Construction's real estate division leverages our deep construction expertise to identify, acquire and develop properties that deliver exceptional value — whether for owner-occupiers, investors or development partners.</p>
    <p>Our unique position as both a construction company and property specialist means we see opportunities others miss. We can accurately assess a property's development potential, estimate renovation or construction costs with precision and deliver completed projects that maximise return on investment.</p>

    <h3>Our Real Estate Services</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Land acquisition for residential and commercial development</li>
      <li>Property acquisition — renovation and resale opportunities</li>
      <li>Development feasibility analysis and due diligence</li>
      <li>Sale of completed developments — apartments, houses and commercial units</li>
      <li>Joint venture partnerships for larger development projects</li>
      <li>Investment property advisory</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Market Knowledge</h3>
    <p>Operating across Luxembourg since 2009, we have built an extensive knowledge of local property markets — from the premium neighbourhoods of Luxembourg City (Belair, Limpertsberg, Kirchberg) to the growing communities of the north (Ettelbruck, Diekirch, Mersch) and the Moselle region. This granular market knowledge allows us to identify sites with strong development potential before they reach the open market.</p>
    <p>We track zoning changes, commune development plans (PAG revisions) and infrastructure projects that influence property values, giving our clients and partners an informed edge in their investment decisions.</p>

    <h3>Due Diligence &amp; Risk Assessment</h3>
    <p>Every acquisition is supported by thorough due diligence. We assess zoning status, development density permitted under the PAG, access to utilities, soil conditions, environmental constraints and any legal encumbrances. Our construction expertise allows us to provide realistic cost estimates for development or renovation, ensuring that financial projections are grounded in practical reality rather than optimistic assumptions.</p>

    <h3>The Builder's Advantage</h3>
    <p>When SAM Construction acquires property for development, we control the entire value chain — from purchase through design, construction and sale. This vertical integration eliminates margin stacking between separate developers and contractors, delivering better value for end buyers and stronger returns on the investment. It also means tighter quality control, faster project delivery and a single point of accountability throughout.</p>

    <h3>Compliance &amp; Legal Framework</h3>
    <p>Luxembourg property transactions involve specific legal requirements, including notarial procedures, registration duties and compliance with anti-money laundering regulations. We work with established Luxembourg notaries and legal advisors to ensure every transaction is properly structured, tax-efficient and fully compliant with the Grand Duchy's legal framework.</p>
